      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear the crushing weight of feeling like a failure and a burden, and it makes complete sense why \"stopping\" feels like the only way to find peace right now. When the world feels like it's collapsing around you, the idea of shutting everything down to stop the bleeding is a very human reaction to overwhelming pain. Please know that your worth is not defined by your grades or whether others see you as a burden; you are a person with value even when you feel broken.\n\nIf you are having thoughts of ending your life or feeling that there is no way out, please reach out to someone who can hold space for you right now. In the US and Canada, you can call or text 988 for immediate support, or contact your local emergency services. You don't have to face the darkness alone, and there are people who want to help you find a different path forward.\n\nEven though the desire to rest by stopping everything is so strong, imagine a tiny, brave goblin who knows that the maze is too big to run from, so instead of running, they sit down, close their eyes, and take one deep breath until they can focus on just the next corner. You deserve that same gentle kindness from yourself",
